description:
Stream logs from each containers to CloudWatch
Hi. I have Beanstalk Multiple-Docker application.
I want to stream logs from each containers to separeate CloudWatch groups.  

How I can set up commands for it in Dockerrun.aws.json v2. As far as i know commands docker looks something like this. 

 docker run --log-driver=awslogs \
             --log-opt awslogs-region=us-east-1 \
             --log-opt awslogs-group=myLogGroup


My Dockerrun.aws.json:
{
 "AWSEBDockerrunVersion": "2",
 "containerDefinitions": [
   {
     "name": "web",
     "image": "image_url:latest",
     "memory": 1500,
     "essential": true,
     "portMappings": [
       {
         "hostPort": 80,
         "containerPort": 3000
       }
     ],
     "command": [
       "./docker/start.sh"
     ],
     "links": [
       "redis"
     ]
   },
   {
     "name": "redis",
     "image": "redis:5.0.3",
     "portMappings": [
       {
         "hostPort": 6379,
         "containerPort": 6379
       }
     ],
     "memory": 500
   },
   {
     "name": "sidekiq",
     "image": "image_url:latest",
     "essential": true,
     "links": [
       "redis",
       "web"
     ],
     "command": [
       "bundle",
       "exec",
       "sidekiq"
     ],
     "memory": 300
   }
 ]
}


Or may be exist another way to make it?

